Scope
This skill governs every list/collection surface in an Android app. It begins where data arrives at the UI layer and ends when pixels are rendered on screen. It does not own networking, database queries, ViewModels, or business logic.

Quick Decision Tree
Need a list/grid/collection?
│
├─ Single item type           → GenericListAdapter       (see §A)
├─ Multiple item types        → SealedItemAdapter        (see §B)
├─ Large / paginated dataset  → PagingDataAdapter        (see §C)
├─ Nested horizontal rows     → NestedAdapter            (see §D)
├─ Section headers + items    → ConcatAdapter            (see §E)
│
├─ Swipe-to-delete / actions  → ItemTouchHelper          (see §F)
├─ Drag-and-drop reorder      → ItemTouchHelper drag     (see §F)
├─ Item selection             → SelectionTracker         (see §G)
│
└─ Empty / loading / error    → LoadStateAdapter / StateView (see §H)

Mandatory Rules
These rules apply to every implementation without exception.

#	Rule
R1	Always use ListAdapter<T, VH> unless Paging 3 is required; then use PagingDataAdapter<T, VH>. Never use raw RecyclerView.Adapter for new code.
R2	Always provide a DiffUtil.ItemCallback<T>. See §I for canonical implementations.
R3	Never perform work inside onBindViewHolder() that can be done outside it — no string formatting, no date parsing, no Bitmap decoding. Pre-compute in the data/mapper layer.
R4	Never hold a reference to Activity, Fragment, or ViewModel inside an Adapter. Pass callbacks (() -> Unit, (T) -> Unit) via the constructor.
R5	Use ViewBinding for every ViewHolder. Never use findViewById in new code.
R6	Enable stable IDs (setHasStableIds(true)) only when each item has a guaranteed-unique, immutable Long ID. Do not fabricate IDs.
R7	Cancel image loads, remove listeners, and clear animation handles inside onViewRecycled().
R8	Image loading must use Coil (preferred) or Glide — never BitmapFactory on the main thread.
R9	DiffUtil diff calculation is automatic inside ListAdapter. Do not call DiffUtil.calculateDiff manually unless using a raw adapter.
R10	Call setHasFixedSize(true) when item count changes do not affect the RecyclerView's own dimensions.
R11	Never call notifyDataSetChanged(). Use submitList, notifyItemChanged(pos, payload), or notifyItem{Inserted,Removed,Moved}.
R12	Use bindingAdapterPosition (not adapterPosition or layoutPosition) inside click listeners. Guard with != RecyclerView.NO_ID.
Implementation Checklist
Verify every item before marking an implementation complete.

Adapter
 Extends ListAdapter or PagingDataAdapter
 DiffUtil.ItemCallback is correct (see §I)
 onCreateViewHolder inflates via ViewBinding only
 onBindViewHolder does zero I/O, zero allocation, zero computation
 Click/action events delegated via constructor callbacks
 onViewRecycled clears image loads and listeners
 No direct ViewModel / Activity / Fragment references
RecyclerView host (Fragment / Activity)
 LayoutManager set before adapter
 setHasFixedSize(true) where applicable
 itemAnimator disabled (= null) for chat-style or frequently-updating lists to prevent flicker
 RecycledViewPool shared between sibling RecyclerViews if present
 addItemDecoration used for spacing instead of hardcoded layout_margin on item roots
State handling
 Empty state shown when currentList.isEmpty() and not loading
 Loading state shown before first submitList
 Error state surfaced and retry offered when upstream fails
 See §H for patterns
Performance
 Prefetch enabled (initialPrefetchItemCount for nested RVs, setItemViewCacheSize if needed)
 Images bounded to view size — no full-resolution decodes
 See §J for the full performance audit checklist
Accessibility
 Each item has a logical contentDescription
 Custom touch targets ≥ 48 dp
 Focus order is predictable
 See §K for full accessibility patterns
Dependency Reference
Add to app/build.gradle.kts as needed:

android {
    buildFeatures { viewBinding = true }
}
dependencies {
    // Core
    implementation("androidx.recyclerview:recyclerview:1.3.2")
    // Paging 3 — only when dataset is server/db paginated
    implementation("androidx.paging:paging-runtime-ktx:3.3.4")
    // Multi-select with keyboard + mouse support
    implementation("androidx.recyclerview:recyclerview-selection:1.1.0")
    // Image loading (preferred)
    implementation("io.coil-kt:coil:2.7.0")
    // Swipe/drag — built into RecyclerView, no extra dep needed
}

§A — Single View Type (GenericListAdapter)
Baseline pattern for any homogeneous list.

// ui/list/ItemAdapter.kt
class ItemAdapter(
    private val onItemClick: (Item) -> Unit,
    private val onItemLongClick: (Item) -> Boolean = { false },
) : ListAdapter<Item, ItemAdapter.ViewHolder>(ItemDiffCallback()) {
    override fun onCreateViewHolder(parent: ViewGroup, viewType: Int): ViewHolder {
        val binding = ListItemBinding.inflate(
            LayoutInflater.from(parent.context), parent, false
        )
        return ViewHolder(binding)
    }
    override fun onBindViewHolder(holder: ViewHolder, position: Int) {
        holder.bind(getItem(position))
    }
    // Partial bind — only redraw changed fields when a payload is present
    override fun onBindViewHolder(holder: ViewHolder, position: Int, payloads: List<Any>) {
        if (payloads.isEmpty()) {
            super.onBindViewHolder(holder, position, payloads)
            return
        }
        val item = getItem(position)
        @Suppress("UNCHECKED_CAST")
        (payloads.first() as? Set<String>)?.forEach { key ->
            when (key) {
                "title"    -> holder.binding.titleText.text = item.title
                "subtitle" -> holder.binding.subtitleText.text = item.subtitle
                "imageUrl" -> holder.binding.imageView.load(item.imageUrl)
            }
        }
    }
    override fun onViewRecycled(holder: ViewHolder) {
        super.onViewRecycled(holder)
        holder.binding.imageView.dispose() // Coil: cancel in-flight load
    }
    inner class ViewHolder(val binding: ListItemBinding) :
        RecyclerView.ViewHolder(binding.root) {
        init {
            binding.root.setOnClickListener {
                val pos = bindingAdapterPosition
                if (pos != RecyclerView.NO_ID) onItemClick(getItem(pos))
            }
            binding.root.setOnLongClickListener {
                val pos = bindingAdapterPosition
                if (pos != RecyclerView.NO_ID) onItemLongClick(getItem(pos)) else false
            }
        }
        fun bind(item: Item) {
            binding.titleText.text = item.title
            binding.subtitleText.text = item.subtitle
            binding.imageView.load(item.imageUrl) {
                crossfade(true)
                placeholder(R.drawable.ic_placeholder)
                error(R.drawable.ic_error)
            }
            binding.root.contentDescription =
                itemView.context.getString(R.string.item_a11y_desc, item.title)
        }
    }
}
// Fragment / Activity setup
binding.recyclerView.apply {
    layoutManager = LinearLayoutManager(context)
    adapter = ItemAdapter(
        onItemClick = { item -> viewModel.onItemSelected(item.id) }
    )
    setHasFixedSize(true)
}
// Observe and submit
viewLifecycleOwner.lifecycleScope.launch {
    viewModel.items.collect { list ->
        (binding.recyclerView.adapter as ItemAdapter).submitList(list)
    }
}

§B — Multiple View Types (SealedItemAdapter)
Model heterogeneous items with a sealed class. Switch on view type using named constants.

// Sealed model — one sealed hierarchy per adapter
sealed class FeedItem {
    data class Header(val title: String, val subtitle: String) : FeedItem()
    data class Post(val id: Long, val body: String, val authorName: String) : FeedItem()
    data class Banner(val imageUrl: String, val actionLabel: String) : FeedItem()
    data object Divider : FeedItem()
}
class FeedAdapter(
    private val onPostClick: (FeedItem.Post) -> Unit,
    private val onBannerAction: (FeedItem.Banner) -> Unit,
) : ListAdapter<FeedItem, RecyclerView.ViewHolder>(FeedDiffCallback()) {
    override fun getItemViewType(position: Int): Int = when (getItem(position)) {
        is FeedItem.Header  -> TYPE_HEADER
        is FeedItem.Post    -> TYPE_POST
        is FeedItem.Banner  -> TYPE_BANNER
        is FeedItem.Divider -> TYPE_DIVIDER
    }
    override fun onCreateViewHolder(parent: ViewGroup, viewType: Int): RecyclerView.ViewHolder {
        val inflater = LayoutInflater.from(parent.context)
        return when (viewType) {
            TYPE_HEADER  -> HeaderViewHolder(ItemHeaderBinding.inflate(inflater, parent, false))
            TYPE_POST    -> PostViewHolder(ItemPostBinding.inflate(inflater, parent, false))
            TYPE_BANNER  -> BannerViewHolder(ItemBannerBinding.inflate(inflater, parent, false))
            TYPE_DIVIDER -> DividerViewHolder(ItemDividerBinding.inflate(inflater, parent, false))
            else -> error("Unknown viewType $viewType")
        }
    }
    override fun onBindViewHolder(holder: RecyclerView.ViewHolder, position: Int) {
        when (val item = getItem(position)) {
            is FeedItem.Header  -> (holder as HeaderViewHolder).bind(item)
            is FeedItem.Post    -> (holder as PostViewHolder).bind(item)
            is FeedItem.Banner  -> (holder as BannerViewHolder).bind(item)
            is FeedItem.Divider -> Unit // purely static; no bind needed
        }
    }
    // --- ViewHolders ---
    inner class PostViewHolder(private val binding: ItemPostBinding) :
        RecyclerView.ViewHolder(binding.root) {
        init {
            binding.root.setOnClickListener {
                val pos = bindingAdapterPosition
                if (pos != RecyclerView.NO_ID) onPostClick(getItem(pos) as FeedItem.Post)
            }
        }
        fun bind(item: FeedItem.Post) {
            binding.bodyText.text = item.body
            binding.authorText.text = item.authorName
        }
    }
    inner class BannerViewHolder(private val binding: ItemBannerBinding) :
        RecyclerView.ViewHolder(binding.root) {
        init {
            binding.actionButton.setOnClickListener {
                val pos = bindingAdapterPosition
                if (pos != RecyclerView.NO_ID) onBannerAction(getItem(pos) as FeedItem.Banner)
            }
        }
        fun bind(item: FeedItem.Banner) {
            binding.actionButton.text = item.actionLabel
            binding.bannerImage.load(item.imageUrl)
        }
    }
    inner class HeaderViewHolder(private val binding: ItemHeaderBinding) :
        RecyclerView.ViewHolder(binding.root) {
        fun bind(item: FeedItem.Header) {
            binding.titleText.text = item.title
            binding.subtitleText.text = item.subtitle
        }
    }
    class DividerViewHolder(binding: ItemDividerBinding) :
        RecyclerView.ViewHolder(binding.root)
    companion object {
        private const val TYPE_HEADER  = 0
        private const val TYPE_POST    = 1
        private const val TYPE_BANNER  = 2
        private const val TYPE_DIVIDER = 3
    }
}

§C — Paging 3 (PagingDataAdapter)
Drop-in replacement for ListAdapter when data is loaded from a paged source.

class PostPagingAdapter(
    private val onPostClick: (Post) -> Unit,
) : PagingDataAdapter<Post, PostPagingAdapter.ViewHolder>(PostDiffCallback()) {
    override fun onCreateViewHolder(parent: ViewGroup, viewType: Int) =
        ViewHolder(ItemPostBinding.inflate(LayoutInflater.from(parent.context), parent, false))
    // getItem may return null for placeholders — always guard
    override fun onBindViewHolder(holder: ViewHolder, position: Int) {
        getItem(position)?.let { holder.bind(it) }
    }
    inner class ViewHolder(private val binding: ItemPostBinding) :
        RecyclerView.ViewHolder(binding.root) {
        init {
            binding.root.setOnClickListener {
                val pos = bindingAdapterPosition
                if (pos != RecyclerView.NO_ID) getItem(pos)?.let(onPostClick)
            }
        }
        fun bind(post: Post) {
            binding.titleText.text = post.title
        }
    }
}
// Fragment setup with load-state footer
val pagingAdapter = PostPagingAdapter(onPostClick = { viewModel.onPostSelected(it.id) })
binding.recyclerView.adapter = pagingAdapter.withLoadStateFooter(
    DefaultLoadStateAdapter(pagingAdapter::retry)
)
viewLifecycleOwner.lifecycleScope.launch {
    viewModel.pagedPosts.collectLatest { pagingData ->
        pagingAdapter.submitData(pagingData)
    }
}
// Observe load state for header UI (empty / error / loading)
viewLifecycleOwner.lifecycleScope.launch {
    pagingAdapter.loadStateFlow.collectLatest { states ->
        val refresh = states.refresh
        binding.progressBar.isVisible = refresh is LoadState.Loading
        binding.errorView.isVisible   = refresh is LoadState.Error
        binding.emptyView.isVisible   =
            refresh is LoadState.NotLoading && pagingAdapter.itemCount == 0
    }
}

§D — Nested RecyclerView
Horizontal inner lists inside a vertical outer list. Critical: share a RecycledViewPool and call setInitialPrefetchItemCount.

class OuterAdapter(
    private val sharedPool: RecyclerView.RecycledViewPool,
) : ListAdapter<OuterItem, OuterAdapter.ViewHolder>(OuterDiffCallback()) {
    override fun onCreateViewHolder(parent: ViewGroup, viewType: Int) =
        ViewHolder(ItemOuterBinding.inflate(LayoutInflater.from(parent.context), parent, false))
    override fun onBindViewHolder(holder: ViewHolder, position: Int) =
        holder.bind(getItem(position))
    // Reset scroll position so recycled rows don't appear mid-scroll
    override fun onViewRecycled(holder: ViewHolder) {
        super.onViewRecycled(holder)
        holder.binding.innerRecyclerView.scrollToPosition(0)
    }
    inner class ViewHolder(val binding: ItemOuterBinding) :
        RecyclerView.ViewHolder(binding.root) {
        private val innerAdapter = InnerAdapter()
        init {
            binding.innerRecyclerView.apply {
                layoutManager = LinearLayoutManager(
                    binding.root.context, LinearLayoutManager.HORIZONTAL, false
                ).also { it.initialPrefetchItemCount = 4 }
                adapter = innerAdapter
                setRecycledViewPool(sharedPool)
            }
        }
        fun bind(item: OuterItem) {
            innerAdapter.submitList(item.children)
        }
    }
}
// Fragment
val sharedPool = RecyclerView.RecycledViewPool()
binding.outerRecyclerView.adapter = OuterAdapter(sharedPool)

§E — Section Headers via ConcatAdapter
Compose independent adapters without modifying either.

class SectionHeaderAdapter(private val title: String) :
    RecyclerView.Adapter<SectionHeaderAdapter.ViewHolder>() {
    override fun getItemCount() = 1
    override fun onCreateViewHolder(parent: ViewGroup, viewType: Int) =
        ViewHolder(ItemSectionHeaderBinding.inflate(LayoutInflater.from(parent.context), parent, false))
    override fun onBindViewHolder(holder: ViewHolder, position: Int) {
        holder.binding.headerText.text = title
    }
    class ViewHolder(val binding: ItemSectionHeaderBinding) :
        RecyclerView.ViewHolder(binding.root)
}
// Fragment — compose independently
val recentHeader  = SectionHeaderAdapter("Recent")
val recentAdapter = ItemAdapter(onItemClick = { ... })
val popularHeader  = SectionHeaderAdapter("Popular")
val popularAdapter = ItemAdapter(onItemClick = { ... })
binding.recyclerView.adapter = ConcatAdapter(
    recentHeader,  recentAdapter,
    popularHeader, popularAdapter,
)
recentAdapter.submitList(recentItems)
popularAdapter.submitList(popularItems)

§F — Swipe Actions & Drag-and-Drop (ItemTouchHelper)
fun buildItemTouchHelper(
    adapter: ItemAdapter,
    onSwipeLeft:  (Int) -> Unit,
    onSwipeRight: (Int) -> Unit,
    onMoved:      (from: Int, to: Int) -> Unit,
): ItemTouchHelper {
    val callback = object : ItemTouchHelper.SimpleCallback(
        /* dragDirs  */ ItemTouchHelper.UP or ItemTouchHelper.DOWN,
        /* swipeDirs */ ItemTouchHelper.LEFT or ItemTouchHelper.RIGHT,
    ) {
        override fun onMove(
            recyclerView: RecyclerView,
            viewHolder: RecyclerView.ViewHolder,
            target: RecyclerView.ViewHolder,
        ): Boolean {
            onMoved(viewHolder.bindingAdapterPosition, target.bindingAdapterPosition)
            return true
        }
        override fun onSwiped(viewHolder: RecyclerView.ViewHolder, direction: Int) {
            val pos = viewHolder.bindingAdapterPosition
            when (direction) {
                ItemTouchHelper.LEFT  -> onSwipeLeft(pos)
                ItemTouchHelper.RIGHT -> onSwipeRight(pos)
            }
        }
        override fun onChildDraw(
            c: Canvas, recyclerView: RecyclerView,
            viewHolder: RecyclerView.ViewHolder,
            dX: Float, dY: Float, actionState: Int, isCurrentlyActive: Boolean,
        ) {
            // Draw swipe background / icon here before calling super
            super.onChildDraw(c, recyclerView, viewHolder, dX, dY, actionState, isCurrentlyActive)
        }
    }
    return ItemTouchHelper(callback)
}
// Attach in Fragment
val touchHelper = buildItemTouchHelper(
    adapter       = itemAdapter,
    onSwipeLeft   = { pos -> viewModel.deleteItem(itemAdapter.currentList[pos].id) },
    onSwipeRight  = { pos -> viewModel.archiveItem(itemAdapter.currentList[pos].id) },
    onMoved       = { from, to -> viewModel.reorderItems(from, to) },
)
touchHelper.attachToRecyclerView(binding.recyclerView)

§G — Item Selection (SelectionTracker)
// Requires: implementation("androidx.recyclerview:recyclerview-selection:1.1.0")
class SelectableItemAdapter : ListAdapter<Item, SelectableItemAdapter.ViewHolder>(ItemDiffCallback()) {
    var tracker: SelectionTracker<Long>? = null
    override fun onCreateViewHolder(parent: ViewGroup, viewType: Int) =
        ViewHolder(ListItemBinding.inflate(LayoutInflater.from(parent.context), parent, false))
    override fun onBindViewHolder(holder: ViewHolder, position: Int) {
        val item = getItem(position)
        holder.bind(item, tracker?.isSelected(item.id) ?: false)
    }
    inner class ViewHolder(private val binding: ListItemBinding) :
        RecyclerView.ViewHolder(binding.root) {
        fun bind(item: Item, isSelected: Boolean) {
            binding.root.isActivated = isSelected // drives activated-state drawable
            binding.titleText.text   = item.title
            binding.checkmark.isVisible = isSelected
        }
        fun getItemDetails() = object : ItemDetailsLookup.ItemDetails<Long>() {
            override fun getPosition(): Int = bindingAdapterPosition
            override fun getSelectionKey(): Long = getItem(bindingAdapterPosition).id
        }
    }
}
// Fragment
val adapter = SelectableItemAdapter()
binding.recyclerView.adapter = adapter
val selectionTracker = SelectionTracker.Builder(
    "item-selection",
    binding.recyclerView,
    StableIdKeyProvider(binding.recyclerView),
    object : ItemDetailsLookup<Long>() {
        override fun getItemDetails(e: MotionEvent) =
            binding.recyclerView.findChildViewUnder(e.x, e.y)?.let {
                (binding.recyclerView.getChildViewHolder(it) as SelectableItemAdapter.ViewHolder)
                    .getItemDetails()
            }
    },
    StorageStrategy.createLongStorage()
).withSelectionPredicate(SelectionPredicates.createSelectAnything())
 .build()
adapter.tracker = selectionTracker
selectionTracker.addObserver(object : SelectionTracker.SelectionObserver<Long>() {
    override fun onSelectionChanged() {
        val selected = selectionTracker.selection.toList()
        if (selected.isNotEmpty()) viewModel.onSelectionChanged(selected)
        else viewModel.onSelectionCleared()
    }
})

§H — State Management (Empty / Loading / Error)
Pattern A — Overlay views (simplest, works for all adapter types)
// In Fragment — observe state from ViewModel
viewLifecycleOwner.lifecycleScope.launch {
    viewModel.uiState.collect { state ->
        binding.progressBar.isVisible = state is UiState.Loading
        binding.errorView.isVisible   = state is UiState.Error
        binding.emptyView.isVisible   = state is UiState.Empty
        binding.recyclerView.isVisible = state is UiState.Success
        if (state is UiState.Success) adapter.submitList(state.items)
        if (state is UiState.Error)   binding.retryButton.setOnClickListener { viewModel.retry() }
    }
}
sealed class UiState<out T> {
    data object Loading : UiState<Nothing>()
    data object Empty   : UiState<Nothing>()
    data class  Success<T>(val items: List<T>) : UiState<T>()
    data class  Error(val message: String, val cause: Throwable? = null) : UiState<Nothing>()
}

Pattern B — LoadStateAdapter footer (Paging 3)
class DefaultLoadStateAdapter(
    private val retry: () -> Unit,
) : LoadStateAdapter<DefaultLoadStateAdapter.ViewHolder>() {
    override fun onCreateViewHolder(parent: ViewGroup, loadState: LoadState) =
        ViewHolder(ItemLoadStateBinding.inflate(LayoutInflater.from(parent.context), parent, false))
    override fun onBindViewHolder(holder: ViewHolder, loadState: LoadState) {
        holder.binding.progressBar.isVisible = loadState is LoadState.Loading
        holder.binding.retryButton.isVisible  = loadState is LoadState.Error
        holder.binding.errorText.isVisible    = loadState is LoadState.Error
        if (loadState is LoadState.Error) {
            holder.binding.errorText.text = loadState.error.localizedMessage
            holder.binding.retryButton.setOnClickListener { retry() }
        }
    }
    class ViewHolder(val binding: ItemLoadStateBinding) :
        RecyclerView.ViewHolder(binding.root)
}

Pattern C — Inline state items (multi-type adapter)
Add Loading, Error, and Empty as sealed variants to your FeedItem type (see §B). The adapter renders them as view types. The ViewModel maps upstream state to the appropriate list (e.g., listOf(FeedItem.Loading) while fetching, then the real list on success).

§I — DiffUtil Patterns
Standard ItemCallback (data class with stable ID)
class ItemDiffCallback : DiffUtil.ItemCallback<Item>() {
    // Are these the same logical item? Use the stable unique ID — never compare full objects here.
    override fun areItemsTheSame(oldItem: Item, newItem: Item): Boolean =
        oldItem.id == newItem.id
    // Has the content changed? data class structural equality is correct here.
    override fun areContentsTheSame(oldItem: Item, newItem: Item): Boolean =
        oldItem == newItem
    // Return minimal change-set as payload to enable partial binding.
    override fun getChangePayload(oldItem: Item, newItem: Item): Any? {
        val diff = mutableSetOf<String>()
        if (oldItem.title    != newItem.title)    diff.add("title")
        if (oldItem.subtitle != newItem.subtitle) diff.add("subtitle")
        if (oldItem.imageUrl != newItem.imageUrl) diff.add("imageUrl")
        if (oldItem.badge    != newItem.badge)    diff.add("badge")
        return if (diff.isEmpty()) null else diff
    }
}

Sealed class ItemCallback (multi-type adapter)
class FeedDiffCallback : DiffUtil.ItemCallback<FeedItem>() {
    override fun areItemsTheSame(oldItem: FeedItem, newItem: FeedItem): Boolean =
        when {
            oldItem is FeedItem.Post    && newItem is FeedItem.Post    -> oldItem.id == newItem.id
            oldItem is FeedItem.Header  && newItem is FeedItem.Header  -> oldItem.title == newItem.title
            oldItem is FeedItem.Banner  && newItem is FeedItem.Banner  -> oldItem.imageUrl == newItem.imageUrl
            oldItem is FeedItem.Divider && newItem is FeedItem.Divider -> true
            else -> false // different types are never the same item
        }
    override fun areContentsTheSame(oldItem: FeedItem, newItem: FeedItem): Boolean =
        oldItem == newItem
}

Common DiffUtil Bugs
Bug	Symptom	Cause	Fix
Items don't animate	Everything blinks on update	areItemsTheSame always false	Use stable unique ID, not full equality
Items never update	Stale UI after submitList	areContentsTheSame always true	Ensure data class equals covers all displayed fields
Wrong item updates	Adjacent item flickers	Mutable objects mutated before submitList	Use immutable data — copy the list, never mutate in place
Crash IndexOutOfBounds	Random crash during animation	notifyDataSetChanged() mixed with submitList	Never mix manual notify calls with ListAdapter
§J — Performance Audit Checklist
RecyclerView setup
setHasFixedSize(true) — set whenever item count changes don't affect RV dimensions
itemAnimator = null — disable for high-frequency update lists (chat, live feeds)
setItemViewCacheSize(n) — increase (default 2) for lists where users rapidly scroll back
LayoutManager
LinearLayoutManager — standard vertical/horizontal; ensure initialPrefetchItemCount is set for nested RVs
GridLayoutManager(ctx, spanCount) — set spanSizeLookup for headers that span all columns
StaggeredGridLayoutManager — use gapStrategy = GAP_HANDLING_MOVE_ITEMS_BETWEEN_SPANS only if needed; it's expensive
onBindViewHolder
// WRONG — string formatting on every bind
holder.binding.label.text = "Item #${item.id} — ${item.title.uppercase()}"
// CORRECT — pre-formatted in the data mapper before submitList
holder.binding.label.text = item.formattedLabel

Image loading
// Coil — always constrain to view size; never decode full-resolution
binding.imageView.load(item.imageUrl) {
    size(ViewSizeResolver(binding.imageView)) // or explicit pixels
    crossfade(true)
    memoryCachePolicy(CachePolicy.ENABLED)
    diskCachePolicy(CachePolicy.ENABLED)
}

Nested RecyclerView
// Share pool between outer items — prevents re-inflation of inner ViewHolders
val sharedPool = RecyclerView.RecycledViewPool().apply {
    setMaxRecycledViews(/* viewType */ 0, /* max */ 20)
}
// Tell prefetcher how many inner items will be visible
innerLayoutManager.initialPrefetchItemCount = 4

Object allocation
// WRONG — creates a new lambda on every bind
holder.binding.root.setOnClickListener { doSomething(item) }
// CORRECT — set once in init{}; capture via bindingAdapterPosition at call time
init {
    binding.root.setOnClickListener {
        val pos = bindingAdapterPosition
        if (pos != RecyclerView.NO_ID) onItemClick(getItem(pos))
    }
}

§K — Accessibility
ContentDescription rules
// Simple item
binding.root.contentDescription = context.getString(
    R.string.a11y_item_desc,   // "Product: %1$s, Price: %2$s"
    item.title,
    item.formattedPrice,
)
// Interactive item with state
binding.favoriteButton.contentDescription = if (item.isFavorited) {
    context.getString(R.string.a11y_remove_favorite, item.title)
} else {
    context.getString(R.string.a11y_add_favorite, item.title)
}
// Announce dynamic changes to TalkBack
binding.root.accessibilityLiveRegion = View.ACCESSIBILITY_LIVE_REGION_POLITE

Touch targets
// Minimum 48 dp touch target — enforce via ViewCompat delegate if the view is smaller
ViewCompat.setAccessibilityDelegate(binding.smallIcon, object : AccessibilityDelegateCompat() {
    override fun onInitializeAccessibilityNodeInfo(
        host: View, info: AccessibilityNodeInfoCompat
    ) {
        super.onInitializeAccessibilityNodeInfo(host, info)
        val density = host.context.resources.displayMetrics.density
        val minTouchPx = (48 * density).toInt()
        info.setBoundsInScreen(Rect(0, 0, minTouchPx, minTouchPx))
    }
})

Focus management during updates
// Restore focus to first changed item after submitList completes
adapter.registerAdapterDataObserver(object : RecyclerView.AdapterDataObserver() {
    override fun onItemRangeInserted(positionStart: Int, itemCount: Int) {
        if (positionStart == 0) binding.recyclerView.scrollToPosition(0)
    }
})

Mandatory checklist
 Every interactive item has a unique, descriptive contentDescription
 Touch targets are ≥ 48 × 48 dp
 Items that change state (checkbox, toggle, favorite) update contentDescription on state change
 Swipe actions have a keyboard/switch-access alternative (long-press or contextual menu)
 Drag-and-drop has an accessible reorder mode (hold + arrow keys or explicit up/down buttons)
 importantForAccessibility is set to no on purely decorative views (dividers, decorations)
Restrictions (Hard Limits)
The skill must never:

Make network calls inside an Adapter or ViewHolder
Query a database or Room DAO from UI layer classes
Read from or write to a ViewModel directly
Execute business logic or data transformations beyond display formatting
Block the main thread (no runBlocking, no BitmapFactory.decodeFile on main)
Allocate objects inside onBindViewHolder (no lambdas, no String.format, no list copies)
Call notifyDataSetChanged() — always use submitList or targeted notifyItem* methods
Hold strong references to Activity, Fragment, Context beyond what ViewBinding requires
